  "full_text_flowing_modernisation_text_block": "And to the presidency of the Supreme Council of Judicial Ordinances, from the greatest viziers of the Sublime Sultanate,\nto His Excellency the illustrious and majestic Hüsrev Muhammed Pasha, who adorns the state, and to the beautiful presidency of\nthe aforesaid council—a service necessitating pride—specifically to him who holds the sublime post of the Grand Vizierate,\nfrom the illustrious ministers of the Sublime State, His Excellency el-Hajj Muhammed Emin Rauf Pasha,\nand to the grave matters of the Serasker-ship of the Regular Soldiers of the Imperial Presence,\nto His Excellency the illustrious Halil Rifat Pasha, who adorns the Ministry of Trade with honor,\nand to the grave service of the aforesaid ministry, the former Serasker, His Excellency Muhammed Said Pasha,\nand to the sublime office of the Marshal of the Imperial Secretariat, with the supreme rank of vizierate,\nand belonging to the glorious father, abundant in praises, the King of Kings, the Lord whose abode is Paradise [Sultan Mahmud II], His Excellency's\nelite imperial courtiers, His Excellency the kindly Riza Bey Efendi,\nand to the stewardship of Her Excellency the illustrious and chaste Valide Sultan [Queen Mother] of high glory,\nher sublime service, with the supreme rank of Marshal, from the great men of the Sublime State, to the supplies\nof war minister, His Excellency the kindly Ali Necib Bey Efendi; in the Imperial Presence\nshowing grace, by His Majesty the Monarch, as it has been commanded to be conferred and favored,\nafter the execution, the supreme personage of the Grand Vizier, together with the officials of the Sublime Porte, from the Garden Gate\nwith a reception, while they commanded the bestowing of rays of glory upon their stations of high qualities,\nthe ceremony of congratulation and felicitation was performed by all the pillars and servants of the Sublime Sultanate,\nand subsequently, in accordance with the requirement of the royal will, accustomed to favor, which was commanded to be attached,\nthat which became vacant from the responsibilities of His Excellency the aforesaid Ali Necib Bey Efendi,\nthe Ministry of Military Supplies, to the Minister of the Council of Lawsuits, one of the veteran men of\nthe Sublime Sultanate, the prosperous Necib Efendi; and the aforesaid ministry [Council of Lawsuits] also, to the most illustrious of the men of\nthe Sublime State, the former Minister of the Imperial Arsenal, the prosperous Hacı Saib Efendi,\nto his Excellency; and the service of the Beylikçi of the Imperial Council, to the Scribe of Internal Petitions,\nthe noble Şekib Efendi; and the service of the Amedci [Receiver] of the Imperial Council, to the [Scribe of] Petitions of\nExternal Affairs, the noble Numan Mahir Bey Efendi; and the External Secretariat also,\nto the former Letter-Writer of External Affairs, the noble Sadullah Enveri Efendi, by conferral,\ntheir offices were executed; and all officials were confirmed in their services and affairs as before,\nand with retention, the ranks of the Internal and External Secretariats also, like the other two affairs [departments] of the Sublime Porte,\nwere transferred to the Second Rank, their registration approved, and their decorations arranged and given accordingly,\nand thus it has been commanded to be executed.\nAs is known to all, whether upon the occurrence of the Imperial Accession, or\nin the change of the sublime office of the Grand Vizierate, the sending of an Imperial Rescript to the Sublime Porte\nis based on the observed rule and the virtue-comprising method of the Sublime Sultanate;\non the third Wednesday day of the honor-familiar accession of His Majesty the King of Kings,\nthe blessed script of grace-points, commanded to be threaded into lines upon white [paper],\nby the Presence of the Refuge of the Caliphate, from the elite close ones of His Majesty the King of Kings, the kindly...",
